After 15+ DevOps interviews, I realized something - you don’t need to learn 100 tools to crack interviews. Just master 20 real fundamentals.

Everyone’s busy chasing the next shiny tool - but interviewers still test how deeply you understand the basics that actually keep systems running.

Here are the 20 areas you really need to master as a DevOps engineer:

